# NLWeb Integration Configuration

## Environment Variables
# Copy this to .env.local in your Docusaurus project root for local development

# NLWeb API Configuration
NLWEB_API_URL=http://localhost:8080

# Azure OpenAI Configuration (for production)
# AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=your-azure-openai-endpoint
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your-api-key
# AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=your-deployment-name

# Production API URL (when deployed)
# NLWEB_API_URL=https://your-domain.com/api

## Development Setup
# 1. Install Python dependencies: pip install -r requirements-api.txt
# 2. Run the NLWeb API: python nlweb-api.py
# 3. Start Docusaurus: npm start
# 4. The chat component will automatically connect to the API

## Production Deployment
# The nlweb-api.py can be deployed as:
# - Azure Functions
# - Azure Container Instances
# - Azure App Service
# - Any other Python hosting service